@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <h4>Introduction</h4>
    <p>
        Welcome to Brickwell, your number one source for cool Lego set builds. We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our customers and visitors, including those who are from the European Union in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
        This Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal information we collect, how it’s used, and the measures we take to protect it.
    </p>
    <h4>Information We Collect</h4>
    <p>
        When you visit Brickwell, we may collect a variety of information, including:
        Personal Identification Information: Name, email address, shipping address, payment information, and other details necessary for processing your orders.
        Browsing Information: Information about your browsing behavior on our website, including the products you view, the time spent on our site, and other engagement metrics.
    </p>
    <h4>How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <p>
        The information we collect is used in the following ways:
        To process transactions and deliver the products you have ordered.
        To improve our website and tailor it to your preferences.
        To communicate with you, such as sending you updates about your order, newsletters, and promotional offers (with your consent).
    </p>
    <h4>Sharing Your Information</h4>
    <p>
        We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personally identifiable information to outside parties, except to those trusted third parties who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or serving our users, so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential.
    </p>
    <h4>GDPR Rights</h4>
    <p>
        If you are a resident of the European Union, you have the following rights under the GDPR:
        The right to access – You have the right to request copies of your personal data from us.
        The right to rectification – You have the right to request that we correct any information you believe is inaccurate or complete information you believe is incomplete.
        The right to erasure – You have the right to request that we erase your personal data, under certain conditions.
        The right to restrict processing – You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.
        The right to object to processing – You have the right to object to our processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.
        The right to data portability – You have the right to request that we transfer the data that we have collected to another organization, or directly to you, under certain conditions.
        If you make a request under the GDPR, we have one month to respond to you. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information below.
    </p>
    <h4>Security</h4>
    <p>
        We are committed to ensuring that your information is secure. In order to prevent unauthorized access or disclosure, we have put in place suitable physical, electronic, and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online.
    </p>
    <h4>Changes to Our Privacy Policy</h4>
    <p>
        We reserve the right to update our Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. We advise you to review this page periodically for any changes.
    </p>
    <h4>Cookie Policy</h4>
    <p>
        We only use necessary cookies on our website to ensure basic functionality. These cookies are essential for the website to operate properly. By using our website, you consent to the use of these necessary cookies.
    </p>
    <h4>Contact Us</h4>
    <p>
        If you have any questions about our Cookie Policy, please contact us at [Your Contact Information].
    </p>
</div>
